cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about panoptic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture that leverages self-attention, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the trade-off between accuracy and efficiency, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). The network is designed to operate in real-time, which suggests that it may have applications in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
